This was delicious, beautiful (jewel colors), easy. I used a mix of blueberries, blackberries, raspberries. The dough was, as some have noted, sticky, but I floured my hands before handling, and worked it on floured freezer paper.

Rating: 2
Good, but needs some tweaking. The dough was very, very sticky, so I added more flour than the recipe called for. Also, the bottom of the biscuits never quite baked--in the future I'd roll them thinner/make less biscuit dough. My cobbler was also quite runny and could have used more cornstarch/tapioca, but that might have been because of the fruit I used (cherries, red raspberries and blackberries).

