Great cobbler-made it with blackberries, peaches and some nectarines. Everyone loved it. Will definitely make it again.

Rating: 4
I had bought a 5# bag of frozen berries at Costco awhile back before fresh berries were in the market, so when I saw this recipe I had to make it. My company really liked it and the lack of fresh berries was not noticable. It will be my "go to recipe for dessert" for any summer gathering. The only thing I would change is adding more cornstarch if you are using frozen berries.

Rating: 4
Really good! I didn't use strawberries-- just blackberries, raspberries, and blueberries. It was really hot in my kitchen and the dough stayed super sticky even with extra flour, so I ended up with one big dough circle instead of the pretty separate pieces.. but who cares when it's covered in ice cream? It was delicious!

Rating: 4
I added one more cup of mixed berries (blackberries, red and yellow raspberries, blueberries and strawberries) and baked in 8 individual ramekins. Did not increase the sugar or cornstarch and it was perfect. Loved the biscuit topping--very tender. Very easy to put together. Served with homemade vanilla ice cream. Absolute hit at a dinner party. This one will go in the "permanent" file!

